	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ummmm, hey!&nbsp;&nbsp;I have an idea!  Why don't you just sit right back down and meditate after you make your pet!  Then have it guard you!  And it's free!<br><br>That blue bar in the corner of your screen? That is your "mana bar". Try saying that: "mana bar".  Very good. It tells you how much magic you have left.  It goes up when you rest, goes down when you cast spells.  Meanwhile, that faithful pet just keeps on protecting you even if you don't know how to properly utilize him.<br><br>Ok, I think that about covers the basics of using magical pets.<br><br>Next time we will discuss the niceties of inter-species relations and why you can not impregnate your pet.<br><br>--Pusbag, who can tell the difference between a skeleton pet and a female troll and appreciates the less bony version.<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
